29/01/2010
ATHENS, Greece -- A small bomb went off Thursday (January 28th) outside a building housing the office of former Prime Minister Costas Simitis in downtown Athens.
Police say it caused minor damage but no injuries.
A small anarchist group called Revolutionary Liberation Action claimed responsibility in an anonymous phone call to Skai TV.
Simitis headed the government from 1996 to 2004.
(ANA-MPA, AP, AFP - 28/01/10)
